Selection Sort is a simple and intuitive sorting algorithm that repeatedly selects the smallest element from the unsorted portion and moves it to the sorted portion.
select minimums and swapping - (from strivers)

ğŸ”¹ How it Works?
1ï¸âƒ£ Find the smallest element in the unsorted part of the array.
2ï¸âƒ£ Swap it with the first element of the unsorted part.
3ï¸âƒ£ Move to the next position and repeat the process until the entire array is sorted!

ğŸ”¹ Characteristics of Selection Sort:
âœ… In-Place Sorting (No extra memory required)
âœ… Not Stable (Relative order of equal elements may change)
âœ… Best for Small Datasets

problem solved : selection sort from GFG 

class Solution: 
    def selectionSort(self, arr):
        #code here
        
        n=len(arr)
        
        for i in range(n-1):
            mini=i
            
            for j in range(i+1,n):
                if arr[j]<arr[mini]:
                    mini = j
                    
            arr[i], arr[mini] = arr[mini], arr[i]

